contentrichtext.text: {{Italic title prefixed|3}} '''USS ''Bainbridge''''' may refer to any of five warships named after the early [[U.S. Navy]] hero [[William Bainbridge]]: *{{USS|Bainbridge|1842}}, was a 12-gun brig commissioned in 1842 and lost off [[Cape Hatteras]] in 1863. *{{USS|Bainbridge|DD-1}}, was the first destroyer of the US Navy, in service from 1902 to 1919. *{{USS|Bainbridge|DD-246}}, was a destroyer, commissioned in 1920 and sold in 1945. *{{USS|Bainbridge|CGN-25}}, was commissioned as a nuclear-powered destroyer leader and in service from 1962 to 1996. *{{USS|Bainbridge|DDG-96}}, is an [[Arleigh Burke class destroyer|''Arleigh Burke''-class]] guided missile destroyer, commissioned on 12 November 2005 and currently in service. {{Shipindex}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Bainbridge}} [[Category:United States Navy ship names]]
